3. If k is greater than 0, update the maximum count accordingly.
4. Return the maximum count.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the input string. The space complexity is O(1) since we only use a constant amount of space for the two helper methods and the main method. The energy implications are low since the solution only performs a constant number of operations and does not require any additional energy consumption.

